other_tests.findings: Enlarged appendix containing fluid with a hyperenhancing wall, consistent with complicated appendicitis. Mild ground glass densities noted within the basilar portion of the right lung base most likely related to atelectasis. No pleural effusion or pulmonary nodule at the bases. Small amount of fluid noted adjacent to the inflamed appendix and within the pelvis. The spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, gallbladder, pancreas, stomach, duodenal loops of small bowel, and large bowel have normal appearance. No free air noted within the abdomen.
